 of modernism for the twenty-first century in ways that will help to recalibrate the field of Expressionist studies for future scholarship. Blaue Reiter still matters, the contributors argue, because the legacies of abstraction are still being debated by artists, writers, philosophers and cultural theorists today.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aArt, Germany20th century. 0aBlaue Reiter (Group of artists). 0aExpressionism (Art)zGermany. 7aART / History / Modern (late 19th Century to 1945).2bisacsh  aAugust Macke.  aExpressionism.  aFranz Marc.  aGabriele Münter.  aGermany.  aPaul Klee.  aWassily Kandinsky.  aabstraction.  aart.  amodern art.1 aBehr, Shulamith, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBourneuf, Annie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKuenzli, Katherine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLewer, Deborah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLong, Rose-Carol Washton, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcGavran, Sarah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPrice, Dorothy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPrice, Dorothy, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aShort, Christopher, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTimpano, Nathan J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWeikop, Christian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2020 eBook-Packagez978311128248040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152612163940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526121639423Coveruhttps://www.de